



To Captain William Cockes. Of the First Company of Rangers.Sir,
[Winchester, 12 May 1756]



Captain Baylis,1 of the Prince-William Militia, will give you this; and leave you a reinforcement of twenty menwith these, and the Detachment of your own company, which has now certainly rejoined you; you will be sufficiently able to send out several scouting parties: And it is my desire, you do your utmost to scour these parts, and protect the people.
You will deliver Mr Baylie2 what carpenters tools you have in the Fort: as he has orders to build a small Fort at the Mouth of Little Capecapon. I am &c.

G:W.


May 12th 1756.
N.B. Take Receipts for the several Tools you deliver the Officers.

